The paper deals with multiple-antenna broadcast channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (IT) community. The use of interference alignment and cooperation among transmit antennas suggests that the paper may also belong to the networked systems (NI) and signal processing (SI) sub-categories. The mention of MIMO systems and the use of vector-space approaches suggest that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (MM) and computational complexity (CC) sub-categories.
